doc.previous: Poets in literate societies have sometimes copied the epic format The earliest surviving European examples are the Argonautica of Apollonius of Rhodes and Virgil s Aeneid which follow both the style and subject matter of Homer Other obvious examples are Nonnus Dionysiaca Tulsidas Sri Ramacharit Manas
